+---
+name: spotify-publication-assets
+description: Plan the per-recipe album cover and Spotify Canvas for streaming distribution of the Suno track.
+---
+
+# Spotify Publication Assets
+
+Use when the operator asks the agent to plan streaming-distribution assets for a Suno track. Produces a single artifact: `agent-recipes/{videoId}/song-cover-plan.json` per `contracts/song-cover.md`.
+
+This work is independent from the TikTok pipeline. The TikTok video ships without these assets.
+
+## Goal
+
+For each track published on Spotify (and similar streaming platforms), produce:
+
+1. an **album cover**, square 1:1 ‚Äî image hero of the dish + brand mascot, kitchen recognizable in the background;
+2. a **Spotify Canvas**, vertical 9:16, 5-8 seconds ‚Äî a continuous-loop food-porn beat that reinforces the brand and bridges the TikTok video and the Spotify listen.
+
+## Spotify Canvas non-negotiable specs
+
+- Duration: 5-8 s (Spotify allows 3-8, Seedance 2 imposes >= 5; we target 5 s by default for cost).
+- Format: vertical 9:16, 1080p (Seedance `1080:1920`, 40 credits/s).
+- No sound (Spotify plays the track over the muted Canvas).
+- Safe area: action centered, NOT in the lower half of the screen (Spotify controls overlay there) and not glued to the edges (some phones crop).
+
+## Continuous loop strategy
+
+- Default mode: continuous loop. First frame and last frame must be visually identical.
+- The Canvas plan declares ONE `loopAnchorReferenceName`. The prompt explicitly says first frame and last frame must match `@<loopAnchorReferenceName>`.
+- The loop anchor MUST be a static, reversible visual moment. The mascot gesture overlays on top and returns to it.
+- Do NOT use Seedance `first_last_frames` mode (it blocks the `references[]` array ‚Äî we need the references).
+- Forbidden inside a continuous loop: irreversible motion (visible cooking, state transformation of the dish, gravitational pour that cannot reset). They kill the loop.
+
+## Mascot policy
+
+- Mascot must appear at least once in the 5-8 s window.
+- Default appearance mode: a discrete reversible gesture (a hand sprinkling, sliding a tool, depositing a finishing topping). The mascot enters frame, does the gesture, leaves frame. The loop anchor is the visual state of the dish without the mascot.
+- Other modes (`silhouette_presence`, `celebration`) are deliberate creative choices for specific recipes.
+- Never name the mascot in the Canvas (no surimpressed text, no graphical element with the name).
+- Never have the mascot mouth to the music (no lipsync ‚Äî Spotify policy).
+
+## Reference reuse vs. new reference
+
+The agent decides whether the existing references planned in `reference-plan.json` cover the visual moment the cover or the Canvas needs.
+
+Prefer reuse:
+
+- `FinalDishVisual` is usually a good loop anchor and a good hero for the cover.
+- `@KitchenIslandDefault` (or any `KitchenIsland*` / `Induction*` / `OvenWide`) carries the kitchen identity.
+- `@CharacterSheet` plus a `@PoseFront` / `@PoseTopDown` etc. lock the mascot identity.
+- Any `recipe_state` reference can be reused ‚Äî its shape does NOT need to match the target output (GPT-Image 2 and Seedance both handle non-square anchors).
+
+Declare a NEW recipe-specific reference (in `reference-plan.json`, `source: "generated_reference_needed"`, per `contracts/reference-image-generation.md`) only when the Canvas or the cover needs a visual moment that no existing reference covers ‚Äî usually a more food-porn intermediate that did not need to ship in the TikTok video (a slow praline pour, a glaze drip, a brittle crack reveal, a hero macro of a topping landing on cream).
+
+When you declare a new reference, list its canonical name in the Canvas `imageReferences` (or the cover `conditioningReferences`) the same way you would for a Seedance segment. The app generates the new reference through the References tab before the cover or Canvas generation runs.
+
+## Album cover direction
+
+- Square 1:1. The app generates at the largest square GPT-Image 2 supports and upscales to 3000x3000 for distribution at download time.
+- Mascot as joy/triumph hero in the frame (this is one of the few places character anchors are encouraged ‚Äî the recipe-state policy that excludes them does NOT apply here).
+- Finished dish hero in front. Food porn beats welcome on the dish.
+- Kitchen recognizable in the background (`@KitchenIslandDefault` or a similar identity anchor).
+- No text on the artwork. Spotify renders title and artist itself.
+- Color palette can be more saturated and stylized than the TikTok segments. Background can include the brand rainbow burst when appropriate.
+
+## Album cover prompt template (guidance, not strict)
+
+```
+A square 1:1 album cover.
+The Licorn mascot is the joyful hero behind the kitchen island: fists raised, eyes squinted with happiness, white hoodie, single horn, pink ponytail.
+Use @CharacterSheet to lock the 2D illustrated identity. Do not redesign or 3D-ify the character.
+Use @KitchenIslandDefault as the background kitchen identity: light terrazzo countertop, black flush induction plate, same cabinet style as the recipe.
+Use @FinalDishVisual (or a more food-porn intermediate) as the hero foreground: <one short dish-only sentence here, ‚â§ 280 characters>.
+Behind the character, a vertical rainbow burst that mirrors the celebration outro motif.
+Stylized food-porn lighting on the dish: amber rim light, faint steam where appropriate, glossy textures.
+No text on the artwork. No logo. No URL. No watermark.
+```
+
+## Spotify Canvas prompt template (guidance, not strict)
+
+```
+Vertical 9:16 food-porn loop, 5 seconds, no slow motion, no rapid cuts.
+The first frame and the last frame must be visually identical to @<loopAnchorReferenceName> so the loop is seamless.
+Continuity lock: the dish state is the same at 0.0 s and at 5.0 s.
+
+Mandatory timing (example for a 5 s discrete gesture loop):
+- 0.0 to 1.5 s: the scene is exactly @<loopAnchorReferenceName>. Static.
+- 1.5 to 3.5 s: the Licorn's hand enters from frame top-right, performs <reversible gesture, e.g. sprinkles caramelized hazelnut crumble> on the dish, leaves frame.
+- 3.5 to 5.0 s: the scene returns to @<loopAnchorReferenceName>. Static.
+
+Use @KitchenIslandDefault as the active hero island view.
+Use @CharacterSheet to lock the 2D mascot identity (do not redesign the character).
+
+Integrated audio: no speech, no voiceover, no music. Only quiet kitchen ambience.
+
+Negatives: no text on screen, no captions, no logo, no URL, no watermark, no human face, no lipsync, no rapid cuts, no intense flashes, no irreversible motion of the dish state, no missing portion at the end, no mascot redesign, no 3D-ification of the mascot, no other species.
+```
+
+## Spotify policy guardrails (must hold)
+
+- No logo, no brand name visible, no URL.
+- No human face talking, singing, or rapping (Canvas is not synced to the music).
+- No lipsync of any kind (mascot included).
+- No rapid cuts, no intense flashes.
+- No text on screen (title and artist are rendered by Spotify).
+- Safe area: keep the action away from the lower half (player controls) and the extreme edges (crop on some phones).
+
+## Cost expectations
+
+- Album cover: GPT-Image 2 default quality. Negligible at 100 covers / year.
+- Canvas: 5-8 s of Seedance 2 1080p = 200-320 credits per regen. Plan for ~1.5 regens average per Canvas.
+
+## Cadence reminder
+
+The brand releases 2 tracks per week ‚Äî about 100 Canvases per year. Each Canvas is custom to its recipe and produced by Recipe2Video alongside the rest of the pipeline.
