@@ -0,0 +1,134 @@
+# Spotify Publication Assets Contract (`song-cover-plan.json`)
+
+This contract defines the per-recipe artifact that drives the Recipe2Video **Cover & Canvas** tab. The artifact lives at:
+
+```txt
+agent-recipes/{videoId}/song-cover-plan.json
+```
+
+It is **optional** in the checkpoint manifest: when absent, the app shows an empty state with a CTA that asks the agent to plan publication assets. When present, the app validates it, syncs it into Supabase, and unlocks operator-driven generation of:
+
+1. an **album cover** (1:1 square, generated by GPT-Image 2 via Runway, upscaled to 3000x3000 by the app);
+2. a **Spotify Canvas** (9:16 vertical, 5-8 s, generated by Seedance 2 via Runway).
+
+Both assets target streaming distribution (Spotify, Apple Music, etc.). They are NOT used by the TikTok pipeline.
+
+## Strict JSON shape (schemaVersion 1)
+
+```json
+{
+  "schemaVersion": 1,
+  "albumCover": {
+    "prompt": "string ‚Äî full GPT-Image 2 prompt; references anchors by @Name",
+    "conditioningReferences": ["KitchenIslandDefault", "CharacterSheet", "FinalDishVisual"],
+    "notes": "optional ‚Äî operator-facing rationale"
+  },
+  "spotifyCanvas": {
+    "prompt": "string ‚Äî Seedance text_to_video prompt with explicit loop instruction",
+    "imageReferences": ["KitchenIslandDefault", "CharacterSheet", "PralineMacroFoodPorn"],
+    "videoReferences": [],
+    "loopAnchorReferenceName": "PralineMacroFoodPorn",
+    "durationSeconds": 5,
+    "mascotAppearanceMode": "discrete_gesture",
+    "notes": "optional"
+  },
+  "qualityChecks": {
+    "noTextOnScreen": true,
+    "noLogoOrUrl": true,
+    "noLipsyncToMusic": true,
+    "mascotAppearsAtLeastOnce": true,
+    "loopAnchorIsAlsoInImageReferences": true,
+    "durationWithinSpotifyWindow": true
+  }
+}
+```
+
+Strict JSON: no comments, no trailing commas, no Markdown fences.
+
+## Field rules
+
+### `schemaVersion`
+
+Must be `1`.
+
+### `albumCover.prompt`
+
+- English, full GPT-Image 2 prompt.
+- Must reference its anchors by `@Name` (the canonical name of each entry in `conditioningReferences`).
+- Square 1:1 framing assumed by the app ‚Äî do NOT write framing instructions like "vertical reference still" that came from the older reference-image contract.
+- No text rendered on the artwork (no title, no artist name, no brand, no URL). Spotify renders metadata itself.
+- Mascot is allowed and encouraged ‚Äî this is one of the few places the character can be hero (joy/triumph). It is NOT a "recipe state" image; the recipe-state conditioning policy that excludes character anchors does NOT apply here.
+
+### `albumCover.conditioningReferences`
+
+- Ordered list of canonical names. The app forwards them to GPT-Image 2 as `referenceImages[]`.
+- Each name must resolve to:
+  - a global library entry in `assets/` (kitchen, character, pose, expression, utensil), OR
+  - a recipe-specific reference already declared in `reference-plan.json` for the same `videoId`.
+- Up to 16 anchors (GPT-Image 2 limit). 3-5 well-chosen ones are typically enough: kitchen + mascot + finished dish (or a more food-porn intermediate).
+- Anchors do NOT need to be square. GPT-Image 2 handles non-square anchors fine.
+- If the agent needs a new recipe-specific image (for example a more food-porn intermediate that does not exist yet), declare it in `reference-plan.json` with `source: "generated_reference_needed"` per `contracts/reference-image-generation.md`, then list its canonical name here. The app generates and approves the new reference through the References tab before the cover can be generated.
+
+### `spotifyCanvas.prompt`
+
+- English, full Seedance 2 `text_to_video` prompt.
+- MUST contain an explicit loop instruction. The first frame and the last frame must be visually identical to the loop anchor reference (referenced by `@loopAnchorReferenceName`). Recommended wording: `the first frame and the last frame must be visually identical to @<loopAnchorReferenceName> for a seamless continuous loop`.
+- The app also appends Spotify policy negatives at generation time if not present (no text, no captions, no logo, no URL, no human face, no lipsync, no rapid cuts, no intense flashes), but the agent SHOULD already include them in the prompt.
+- Mascot must appear at least once in the 5-8 s window. Default mode: a discrete reversible gesture (a hand sprinkling a topping, sliding a tool, depositing a finishing touch) that ends back in the loop-anchor visual state. Full-body celebrations are reserved for recipes where the artistic direction explicitly calls for one.
+- Safe area: composition must keep the action centered, NOT in the lower half of the frame (Spotify controls overlay there).
+- No fast cuts, no intense flashes (Spotify policy).
+
+### `spotifyCanvas.imageReferences`
+
+- Up to 9 entries (Seedance hard cap).
+- Each name must resolve to a global library entry OR a recipe-specific reference for the same `videoId`.
+- `loopAnchorReferenceName` MUST be present in this list.
+
+### `spotifyCanvas.videoReferences`
+
+- Up to 3 entries, combined duration <= 15 s (Seedance hard cap).
+- Optional. Use only when a specific motion needs grounding.
+- `LicornOutroVideo` is appropriate ONLY when the artistic direction is an actual mascot celebration (rare for a Canvas ‚Äî a 3 s explosion of joy does NOT loop). For routine discrete gestures, leave this empty and let the prompt drive the motion.
+
+### `spotifyCanvas.loopAnchorReferenceName`
+
+- Required. Canonical name of the reference that defines both the first and the last frame of the loop.
+- Must also appear in `imageReferences`.
+- Choose a static, reversible visual moment. The Canvas mascot gesture overlays on top of this anchor and returns to it at the end of the loop.
+- Common picks: `FinalDishVisual` (default), or a more food-porn intermediate that the agent has planned in `reference-plan.json` (e.g. a hero macro of praline pour, a glaze drip, a clean cracked-open reveal).
+
+### `spotifyCanvas.durationSeconds`
+
+- Integer in `[5, 8]`. This is the intersection of Spotify Canvas window (3-8 s) and Seedance 2 minimum (5 s).
+- Default 5 s for cost (5 x 40 credits = 200 credits per regen at 1080p).
+
+### `spotifyCanvas.mascotAppearanceMode`
+
+- One of:
+  - `discrete_gesture` (default) ‚Äî a hand or partial appearance executes a reversible gesture on the dish.
+  - `silhouette_presence` ‚Äî the mascot is behind the island or off to the side, present but not centered.
+  - `celebration` ‚Äî full body, reserved for recipes whose artistic direction warrants it (rare).
+- Hint for the operator and for downstream prompt sanity checks. Does NOT change generation parameters.
+
+### `qualityChecks`
+
+All booleans the agent self-attests after writing the plan:
+
+- `noTextOnScreen` ‚Äî neither the cover nor the Canvas renders text.
+- `noLogoOrUrl` ‚Äî no brand mark, no URL on the Canvas.
+- `noLipsyncToMusic` ‚Äî the mascot never mouths to the Suno track (Spotify policy: no synced lipsync).
+- `mascotAppearsAtLeastOnce` ‚Äî Canvas mascot policy.
+- `loopAnchorIsAlsoInImageReferences` ‚Äî structural invariant (also enforced by the app).
+- `durationWithinSpotifyWindow` ‚Äî 5-8 s inclusive.
+
+If any check is `false`, the app emits a warning in the sync log but does not block the upsert. The operator decides whether to override or ask the agent to revise.
+
+## Worked example
+
+See [examples/paris-brest/song-cover-plan.json](../examples/paris-brest/song-cover-plan.json).
+
+## Sync behavior (app side, informative)
+
+- The app reads this artifact via the GitHub artifact service at checkpoint sync, validates it against a Zod schema mirroring this contract, resolves every canonical name against `asset_library` + per-video `reference_assets`, and upserts two rows in the `song_cover_artifacts` table (one per kind).
+- Existing `active_media_asset_id` is preserved on text/ref changes ‚Äî only a manual regen produces a new variant.
+- If `song-cover-plan.json` is missing, the Cover & Canvas page renders an empty state and a CTA "Ask the agent to plan Spotify assets" that sends the agent a `publication_planning` stage message.
